#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Since version 2.5, YunoHost integrates Let's Encrypt certificates automated management. You can easily and freely [install a Let's Encrypt certificate](/admin/domains/certificate). The following document describes the steps for installing a paid certificate from a certification authority (**Gandi**, **RapidSSL**, **StartSSL**, **Cacert**).\n"
msgstr ""
"Depuis la version 2.5, YunoHost intègre la gestion automatisée des "
"certificats Let's Encrypt. Vous pouvez facilement et librement "
"[installer un certificat Let's Encrypt](/admin/domains/certificate). Le "
"document suivant décrit les étapes à suivre pour installer un certificat "
"payant provenant d'une autorité de certification "
"(**Gandi**, **RapidSSL**, **StartSSL**, **Cacert**).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Some changes have taken place which impact the procedures indicated below:\n"
msgstr ""
"Certaines modifications ont été apportées, qui ont une incidence sur les "
"procédures indiquées ci-dessous :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- Metronome group is no longer used directly but ssl-cert.\n"
"- A `/etc/yunohost/certs/DOMAIN.LTD-history/stamp` directory is used to keep each configuration created and a symlink is created.\n"
msgstr ""
"- Le groupe Metronome n'est plus utilisé directement, mais ssl-cert.\n"
"- Un répertoire `/etc/yunohost/certs/DOMAIN.LTD-history/stamp` est utilisé "
"pour conserver chaque configuration créée et un lien symbolique est créé.\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding a signed certificate by an authority (other than Let's Encrypt)"
msgstr "Ajout d'un certificat signé par une autorité (autre que Let's Encrypt)"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "After the certificate creation with your registration authority, you must have a private key, the key file, and a public certificate, the crt file.\n"
msgstr ""
"Après avoir créé le certificat auprès de votre autorité d'enregistrement, "
"vous devez disposer d'une clé privée, du fichier de clé, et d'un certificat "
"public, du fichier crt.\n"

#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note that the key file is very sensitive, it is strictly personal and must be very well secured.\n"
msgstr ""
"Notez que le fichier clé est très sensible, il est strictement personnel et "
"doit être très bien sécurisé.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "These two files should be copied to the server, if they are not already there.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ces deux fichiers doivent être copiés sur le serveur, s'ils ne s'y trouvent "
"pas déjà.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "From Windows, scp can be used with Putty, by downloading the tool [pscp](http://the.earth.li/~sgtatham/putty/latest/x86/pscp.exe)\n"
msgstr ""
"Sous Windows, scp peut être utilisé avec Putty, en téléchargeant l'outil "
"[pscp](http://the.earth.li/~sgtatham/putty/latest/x86/pscp.exe).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As soon as the files are on the server, the rest of the work will be done on it. In [ssh](/admin/command_line) or locally.\n"
"First, create a folder to store the obtained certificates.\n"
msgstr ""
"Dès que les fichiers sont sur le serveur, le reste du opérations "
"s'effectuera directement sur le serveur. Dans [ssh](/admin/command_line) ou "
"localement.\n"
"Commencez par créer un dossier pour stocker les certificats obtenus.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then, go to the parent folder to continue.\n"
msgstr "Ensuite, allez dans le dossier parent pour continuer.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "As a caution, back up the certificates of origin from YunoHost.\n"
msgstr ""
"Par mesure de précaution, sauvegardez les certificats d'origine de YunoHost."
"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Depending on the registration authority, intermediate and root certificates must be obtained.\n"
msgstr ""
"Selon l'autorité d'enregistrement, des certificats intermédiaires et racine "
"doivent être obtenus.\n"

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "StartSSL"
msgstr "StartSSL"

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "RapidSSL"
msgstr "RapidSSL"

#. type: Title ####
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cacert"
msgstr "Cacert"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "Intermediate and root certificates must be combined with the obtained certificate to create a unified certificate chain.\n"
msgstr ""
"Les certificats intermédiaires et racine doivent être combinés avec le "
"certificat obtenu afin de créer une chaîne de certificats unifiée.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "The private key must be converted to `.pem` format.\n"
msgstr "La clé privée doit être convertie au format `.pem`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "To ensure the certificates syntax, check the files contents.\n"
msgstr ""
"Pour vérifier la syntaxe des certificats, vérifiez le contenu des fichiers.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "The certificates and private key should look like this:\n"
msgstr "Les certificats et la clé privée doivent ressembler à ceci :\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finally, secure your certificate files.\n"
msgstr "Enfin, sécurisez vos fichiers de certificats.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now the certificates (two files with the extension `.pem`) must be copied in `/etc/yunohost/certs/DOMAIN.TLD`.\n"
msgstr ""
"Les certificats (deux fichiers avec l'extension `.pem`) doivent maintenant "
"être copiés dans `/etc/yunohost/certs/DOMAIN.TLD`.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reload NGINX configuration to take into account the new certificate.\n"
msgstr ""
"Rechargez la configuration NGINX pour prendre en compte le nouveau "
"certificat.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/80.advanced/45.certificate_custom.mdx:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your certificate is ready. However, you can ensure that it is in place by testing the certificate using the [geocerts](https://www.geocerts.com/ssl_checker).\n"
msgstr ""
"Votre certificat est prêt. Cependant, vous pouvez vous assurer qu'il est en "
"place en le testant à l'aide de [geocerts]"
"(https://www.geocerts.com/ssl_checker).\n"
